 from johnsh rpi edu hugh johnson subject re quicktime movie available article i d mustang johnsh zero six zero four nine three one six one nine three one organization rensselaer polytechnic institute lines three one nntp posting host mustang stu rpi edu in article i wrote i ve used the recently released macintosh application mpeg to quicktime to convert the excellent mpeg canyon mpg into a quicktime movie while anyone who would want this movie is perfectly able to convert it themselves i thought i d let the net know that i d be glad to mail copies of mine out the movie conversion took close to six hours on my poor little iicx in other words unless you ve got a quadra you might not want to tie up your machine in converting this file the movie is a fast fly through of a fractal generated canyon landscape the movie is five eight seconds long and uses the compact video compressor i e quicktime v one five the movie looks okay on eight bit displays and looks absolutely awesome on one six and two four bit displays i d be happy to mail this movie to the first two zero or so people who ask for it the only caveat is you need to be able to receive a nine megabyte mail message the movie was stuff it ed down to seven megs but binhex ruined that party if more then two zero people want this movie then it s just more evidence that the net needs a dedicated quicktime ftp archive site c mon someone s gotta have a spare one two gb drive out there okay i ve received a whole lot of requests for the movie so for simplicity s sake i can t mail out any more than i ve already received as of one six three zero edt tuesday maybe it ll pop up on a site sooner or later hugh johnson johnsh rpi edu rensselaer polytechnic institute welcome to macintosh troy new york usa